HEADWORD: Dryadella
<hw>Dryadella</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a genus of plants comprising
tropical American species usually placed in the genus
<gen>Masdevallia</gen>; they are very dwarf plants having short tufted
and usually unifoliate stems with usually solitary flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Dryadella</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
